content:
Tracks changes that might impact application performance and provides real-time alerts. Monitors for large file additions, complex functions, and performance anti-patterns.

```json
{
  "Notification": [
    {
      "hooks": [
        {
          "type": "command",
          "command": "if [[ \"$CLAUDE_TOOL_NAME\" == 'Edit' ]] || [[ \"$CLAUDE_TOOL_NAME\" == 'Write' ]]; then FILE_SIZE=$(stat -f%z \"$CLAUDE_TOOL_FILE_PATH\" 2>/dev/null || stat -c%s \"$CLAUDE_TOOL_FILE_PATH\" 2>/dev/null || echo '0'); if [ \"$FILE_SIZE\" -gt 50000 ]; then echo '⚠️ PERFORMANCE: Large file detected ('$FILE_SIZE' bytes)'; fi; if grep -E '(setTimeout|setInterval).*[0-9]{4,}' \"$CLAUDE_TOOL_FILE_PATH\" 2>/dev/null; then echo '⚠️ PERFORMANCE: Long timer detected'; fi; if grep -E 'for.*for.*for' \"$CLAUDE_TOOL_FILE_PATH\" 2>/dev/null; then echo '⚠️ PERFORMANCE: Triple nested loop detected'; fi; fi"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
```
